<subSubSection id="322B6A04367080BA604C60D90A15B878" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E961F47A980C194481DDAB023C445613" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F95A7E704F4BC2A9D267B291F766F0F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The oblong-elliptic leaves with long, silvery appressed hairs abaxially are distinct as is the habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC9928B28E44DC67E8F4A1406D1ECB15" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">• Species 180-182 form a group of three Mexican species with a hypocrateriform corolla and a tendency to be leafless at anthesis.</paragraph>
